FBIS3-12498 "drnes041_j_94003" FBIS-NES-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Mar 1994 ARABIAN Peninsula Yemen Fighting Forces `Disengaged' JN0203070794 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 0500 GMT 2 Mar 94 JN0203070794 Amman Radio Jordan Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] A spokesman for the Jordanian-Omani mediation committee in charge of ending fighting between the Yemeni Army units said yesterday evening that the committee has disengaged the warring forces in the southern Governorate of Abyan and reached a cease-fire. He added that the committee managed to bring the situation in the city of Mudiyah in the Abyan Governorate under control and to disengage the two warring parties. He indicated that agreement was reached with the leaders of the two sides to return the military forces to their pre-crisis positions following the signing of the document of pledge and accord in Amman on 20 February. The military committee, composed of Yemeni, Jordanian, and Omani officers, was formed last Sunday. It enjoys the support of Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid. It was tasked to return forces to their previous positions away from the past border areas, end clashes, and merge the northern and southern armies.
